    <div>
      <div class="section-label">Chapter 08</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Choosing a Vector Database</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">Pinecone</div>
      <div class="db-type">Managed / Serverless</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Easiest to start. No infrastructure to manage. Great for startups wanting zero DevOps overhead.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Beginners & MVPs</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">Weaviate</div>
      <div class="db-type">Open-source / Cloud</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Best-in-class hybrid search (BM25 + vector). Built-in modules for auto-embedding. Rich GraphQL API.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Hybrid Search & RAG</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">Qdrant</div>
      <div class="db-type">Open-source / Cloud (Rust)</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Written in Rust — blazing fast. Excellent filtering. Great docs. Very active development community.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Speed + Filtering</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">Milvus</div>
      <div class="db-type">Open-source (Go)</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Designed for billion-scale. GPU support. Battle-tested at Alibaba, Shopee at massive scale.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Billion-scale Enterprise</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">pgvector</div>
      <div class="db-type">PostgreSQL Extension</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Stays inside your existing Postgres database. No new infrastructure. All SQL queries still work perfectly.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Already on Postgres</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">Chroma</div>
      <div class="db-type">Open-source (Local)</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Dead simple to run locally. Great for prototyping and learning. Python-native, zero config.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Development & Learning</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">LanceDB</div>
      <div class="db-type">Embedded / Serverless</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Runs inside your app (no separate server). Columnar storage. Cost-effective for ML workflows.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Embedded & Cost-Sensitive</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-card">
      <div class="db-name">Redis</div>
      <div class="db-type">In-memory + Vector</div>
      <div class="db-desc">Extreme low-latency (&lt;1ms). Combines caching + vector search. Perfect for real-time apps.</div>
      <span class="db-best">Sub-millisecond Latency</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card card-teal">
    <div class="card-title ct-teal">Quick Decision Guide</div>
    <ul class="blist">
      <li><strong>I want the easiest possible start</strong> → Pinecone (managed, no DevOps)</li>
      <li><strong>I'm already on PostgreSQL</strong> → pgvector (zero new infrastructure)</li>
      <li><strong>I'm just learning / prototyping</strong> → Chroma (local, instant setup)</li>
      <li><strong>I need hybrid keyword + vector search</strong> → Weaviate</li>
      <li><strong>I need maximum query speed with filtering</strong> → Qdrant</li>
      <li><strong>I have billions of vectors</strong> → Milvus (battle-tested at scale)</li>
      <li><strong>I need sub-millisecond latency</strong> → Redis (everything in RAM)</li>
      <li><strong>I want no separate server overhead</strong> → LanceDB (embedded)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!--  CH 9 — When NOT to Use                                   -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="ch9">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-icon icon-red">🚫</div>
    <div>
      <div class="section-label">Chapter 09</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">When NOT to Use a Vector Database</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-warn">
    <div class="callout-icon">⚠️</div>
    <div class="callout-body">
      <strong>Don't Over-Engineer</strong>
      Vector databases are powerful but often unnecessary. Using them when simpler tools suffice adds cost, complexity, and operational burden with zero benefit.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid2" style="margin-top:16px">
    <div class="card card-red">
      <div class="card-title ct-red">❌ Fewer than 10,000 vectors</div>
      <p>At this scale, brute-force search takes milliseconds. A vector DB adds infrastructure complexity with zero performance benefit.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--green);font-size:12.5px;margin-top:8px">✅ Use: In-memory search (NumPy, FAISS locally)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-red">
      <div class="card-title ct-red">❌ Exact match is what you need</div>
      <p>"Find all records where country = US and status = active" — that's a filter, not similarity search. Vector DBs handle this poorly.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--green);font-size:12.5px;margin-top:8px">✅ Use: PostgreSQL / MySQL with indexed columns</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-red">
      <div class="card-title ct-red">❌ Metadata filtering dominates</div>
      <p>If 90% of your query logic is metadata filtering and only 10% is semantic, a traditional database does it better and cheaper.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--green);font-size:12.5px;margin-top:8px">✅ Use: Elasticsearch for filtering + light re-ranking</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-red">
      <div class="card-title ct-red">❌ You haven't fixed your chunking</div>
      <p>Bad RAG results are almost always caused by poor document chunking, not the vector DB. No amount of vector magic fixes badly chunked text.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--green);font-size:12.5px;margin-top:8px">✅ Do: Fix semantic chunking with overlap first</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

