<section class="section" id="glossary">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-icon icon-purple">📖</div>
    <div>
      <div class="section-label">Reference</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Glossary of Key Terms</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="glossary">
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">ANN</div><div class="gloss-def">Approximate Nearest Neighbour — fast but approximate version of finding the closest vector</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">BM25</div><div class="gloss-def">Best Match 25 — the classic keyword scoring algorithm used in Elasticsearch and Lucene</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Chunk</div><div class="gloss-def">A piece of a larger document, split into smaller units for embedding and storage</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Cosine Similarity</div><div class="gloss-def">Distance metric measuring the angle between two vectors (0 = identical, 2 = opposite)</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Dense Vector</div><div class="gloss-def">A vector where most values are non-zero; produced by neural embedding models</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Dimension</div><div class="gloss-def">A single number in a vector; modern embeddings typically have 768–3,072 dimensions</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Embedding</div><div class="gloss-def">A vector representation of data (text, image, audio) produced by an ML model</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">HNSW</div><div class="gloss-def">Hierarchical Navigable Small World — most popular index type for fast ANN search in production</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Hybrid Search</div><div class="gloss-def">Combining sparse (keyword) and dense (vector) search results, merged via RRF</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">IVF</div><div class="gloss-def">Inverted File Index — groups vectors into clusters for faster, memory-efficient search</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">KNN</div><div class="gloss-def">K-Nearest Neighbours — finding the K closest vectors to a query (exact version of ANN)</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Multi-tenancy</div><div class="gloss-def">Serving multiple isolated customers from a single database instance</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">PQ</div><div class="gloss-def">Product Quantization — lossy compression technique reducing vector storage by up to 96%</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">RAG</div><div class="gloss-def">Retrieval-Augmented Generation — using vector search to give LLMs access to custom data</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Recall</div><div class="gloss-def">Fraction of true nearest neighbours returned (1.0 = perfect, 0.95 = industry target)</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">RRF</div><div class="gloss-def">Reciprocal Rank Fusion — algorithm for merging multiple ranked search result lists</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Semantic Search</div><div class="gloss-def">Searching by meaning rather than exact keyword matching</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Sparse Vector</div><div class="gloss-def">A vector where most values are zero; used in BM25 / keyword search systems</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Top-K</div><div class="gloss-def">Returning the K most similar results to a query (e.g. Top-5 = 5 closest vectors)</div></div>
    <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Vector Database</div><div class="gloss-def">A database optimised for storing, indexing, and similarity-searching vector embeddings</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

